    **There is no endorsement or sponsorship by any of the listed publications**

    • "My favorite buy of the year is unquestionably my staple high-waisted straight-leg jeans by Citizens of Humanity. They are the perfect, flattering fit and have a cool vintage wash. I cannot tell you the number of times I've worn them in the past year-they're so easy to dress up or down, and I always get compliments whenever I wear them."

      Sarah Kent, London Editor at Business of Fashion

    • "At our market editor Justine Carreon's recommendation, I tried Citizens of Humanity. (...) Whenever I wear them, someone inevitably asks me what brand they are, so now I'm telling everyone. Enjoy!"

      – Leah Chernikoff, Digital Director of ELLE

    • "Mass-production of jeans often results in cutting corners, which is why Citizens of Humanity prides itself on being one of the few denim brands with vertical integration. (...) Sustainability is also a core value of the brand. Using automated machines to maximize efficiency and minimize fabric waste, and lowering water consumption during the production process, Citizens of Humanity is committing themselves to minimize their carbon footprint."

    • "Citizens of Humanity's loyal following speaks for itself. Their fit and overall look make them a beloved brand that you'll be sure to keep inconstant rotation. COH also keeps sustainability as top priority by limiting their waste and gas usage."

      Taylor Ayers, Fashion Editor of Marie Claire

I cannot tell you the number of times I've worn them in the past year-they're so easy to dress up or down, and I always get compliments whenever I wear them."
